                </p>

                <p>
                    <span id="said_no_02897" class="said" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Mrs. Jennings" data-placement="auto top">"Very well indeed! —
                        how prettily she writes! — aye, that was quite proper to let him be
                        off if he would. That was just like Lucy. — Poor soul! I wish I COULD
                        get him a living, with all my heart. — She calls me dear Mrs.
                        Jennings, you see. She is a good-hearted girl as ever lived. — Very
                        well upon my word. That sentence is very prettily turned. Yes, yes, I will
                        go and see her, sure enough. How attentive she is, to think of every body!
